    mapper.writeValue(new File(&quot;/path/to/yaml/file&quot;), example);

Alternatively you can write your object as a string:
    
    // Write object as YAML string
    String yaml = mapper.writeValueAsString(example);

  [1]: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-dataformats-text/tree/master/yaml
