There are multiple ways to achieve same.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;First way:&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    adapter.notifyItemInserted(itemIndex);

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Here, &lt;b&gt; itemIndex &lt;/b&gt; is the position in the array where you want to add a new element. This will not refresh the entire list on the recycler view. &lt;br&gt; 
But will just add this element to that position.

&lt;b&gt;Second Way:&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    arrayData.addAll(insertIndex, items);
    adapter.notifyItemRangeInserted(itemIndex, items.size());

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Third Way:&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    adapter.notifyDataSetChanged();

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

So, like I have mentioned above there are multiple way of updating a list in recycler view

