Error : &quot;A component required a bean named &#39;xyzService&#39; that could not be found.

Resolution : your project would definitely have different package for each classes, so you need to make sure that you configure that in the component scan of the packages in spring boot main class:

**Single package:**

    @ComponentScan(&quot;org.stackoverflow.springboot&quot;)
    @SpringBootApplication
    @PropertySource(value={&quot;classpath:conf.properties&quot;})
    public class MoviemaxApplication implements CommandLineRunner {

**multiple packages:**

    @ComponentScan({&quot;org.stackoverflow.springboot&quot;,&quot;org.stackoverflow.spring&quot;})
    @SpringBootApplication
    public class SpringbootIn10StepsApplication {

While the question is rather ambiguous and not properly formed, for those who got the same error, check you have set the following:

 1. The @Component, @Service or @Repository annotation set up on your class. Spring searches for the @Component annotation; @Service and @Repository serve as specialization for @Component:

        package my.project; 
        @Component 
        public class UserService{}

 2. @ComponentScan(...) annotation, or @SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = ...):

        @SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = &quot;my.project&quot;)
        public class MyApplicationStarter {}

 @ComponentScan(...) is needed, but it&#39;s managed by @SpringBootApplication as well, so there is no need to declare both annotations, use the one that fits your needs. Both @ComponentScan(...) and @SpringBootApplcation(scanBasePackages = ...) allow you to define multiple packages:

 - @ComponentScan({&quot;my.project&quot;, &quot;my.other.path&quot;})

 - @SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = {&quot;my.project&quot;, &quot;my.other.path&quot;})

Also, with @SpringBootApplication you can define specifically one or more classes you want to scan: 
- @SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackageClass = UserService.class)
- @SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackageClass = {UserService.class, AnotherService.class})

