answers.body_markdown:
Probably the error is related to the migration from Oracle to Azure SQL Server.

As you can see in the [source code of the library](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-batch/blob/8f0c510fc7a6da9b71b3646ccb911a79e04490e9/spring-batch-infrastructure/src/main/java/org/springframework/batch/item/database/support/DefaultDataFieldMaxValueIncrementerFactory.java#L76-L111) under the hood Spring Batch uses different strategies when [generating the ids for jobs, job executions, and step executions](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-batch/blob/8f0c510fc7a6da9b71b3646ccb911a79e04490e9/spring-batch-core/src/main/java/org/springframework/batch/core/repository/support/JobRepositoryFactoryBean.java#L161-L195).

In the Oracle case, they use [sequences](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/main/spring-jdbc/src/main/java/org/springframework/jdbc/support/incrementer/OracleSequenceMaxValueIncrementer.java); with SQL Server, they implemented id generation using [tables with an identity column](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/main/spring-jdbc/src/main/java/org/springframework/jdbc/support/incrementer/SqlServerMaxValueIncrementer.java).

The migration process also replicated the different Oracle sequences required by Spring Batch and very likely it is causing the issue when the aforementioned SQL Server id generation strategy tries obtaining the next value.

Please, drop the migrated sequences and create the [three tables](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-batch/blob/main/spring-batch-core/src/main/resources/org/springframework/batch/core/schema-sqlserver.sql) required for SQL Server with the appropriate values:

```sql
CREATE TABLE BATCH_STEP_EXECUTION_SEQ (
  ID BIGINT IDENTITY(&lt;last analogous Oracle sequence value&gt;, 1)
);

CREATE TABLE BATCH_JOB_EXECUTION_SEQ (
  ID BIGINT IDENTITY(&lt;last analogous Oracle sequence value&gt;, 1)
);

CREATE TABLE BATCH_JOB_SEQ (
  ID BIGINT IDENTITY(&lt;last analogous Oracle sequence value&gt;, 1)
);
```

